Commentary Text: Bumrah to Ruturaj Gaikwad, SIX, hey hey hey! This is audacious stuff. This is a world class bowler who is known for yorkers and you just can't put your front foot across and play a sweep shot over backward square leg and that too for a six. What class from Ruturaj Gaikwad today. Bumrah missed the yorker and bowled a low full toss, but that's an unbelievable hit. SKY comes and congratulates Gaikwad for his knock

Commentary Text: Boult to Raina, out Caught by Rahul Chahar!! Oh no! CSK in all sorts of trouble. Rayudu injured and Raina has played an awful start. This is not how you play against a quality bowler. Makes room, and tries to take on Boult once again. Miscues it completely, as the bottom end of his blade comes off in the process. Commentary Text: Moeen Ali to Krunal Pandya, out Krunal Pandya Run Out!! Well, well, well. There's a thin line between a collapse and things going suicidal. Mumbai have clearly made the jump here. So Krunal's tucked this straight to short mid-wicket and very casually run half way down the pitch as if the single were a given. Nope, even Bolt wouldn't have made it. And Tiwary doesn't even try. He refuses, and Krunal's returning dive isn't enough to beat Bravo's flat throw and MSD's whiplash hands. Krunal Pandya run out (Dwayne Bravo/Dhoni) 4(5)

Commentary Text: Hazlewood to Pollard, out Lbw!! Sharp in-nipper. Skidding low. And there's nothing you can do about these. Even if you review. Just dead accurate Hazlewood stuff -- on a good length, on middle-stump and hitting the inside of Pollard's back knee roll deep inside the crease after going past his flick. Three reds. Three dark reds. Surely you don't burn reviews on these, even if you're Pollard, and even if this is CSK! Pollard lbw b Hazlewood 15(14) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Dwayne Bravo to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Raina!! Ah, DJ Bravo. Isn't he tired of picking up wickets? So cool, so nonchalant and he brings out those funky dance moves. Entices Ishan Kishan with a full pitcher outside off and the attempted lofted drive lands straight into the safe hands of Raina at short cover. It seemed to have stopped a touch and Ishan Kishan clearly was expecting more pace from Bravo, wasn't to be. Dhoni at it again. Not often you see short cover and extra-cover in a T20 game and Kishan hit it straight to the former. Ishan Kishan c Raina b Dwayne Bravo 11(10) [4s-1]
